Hoisting in javascript : we can access the variables and functions even before initialized without any error.
Hello World! Let go deep dive into Hoisting in JavaScript

getName() //Namaste JavaScript 
console.log(x); //undefined ->special value.

var x = 7;
function getName(){
    console.log("Namaste JavaScript")
}
console.log(getName) // it will give the whole function as in out put.

special value undefined getting irrespective of error.

if the var x = 7 not declare then it will show error : x is not define.